at|^c@2
^f  ^*b  Open^*n   ^i   ^*bInvite^*n  ^L  ^*bGF^*n    
^f  @-@-@-@-       ^i @-@-@-@-      ^L@-@-@-        
^f   16 - 18       ^i    7 - 8     ^L  9+
^f   ^*b15 - 17    ^i    8 - 9     ^L 10+ ^*n      ^o the most commonly played range   
^f   14 - 16       ^i    9 - 10    ^L 11+
^f   13 - 15       ^i  10 - 11     ^L 12+
^f   12 - 14       ^i  11 - 12     ^L 13+
^f   10 - 12       ^i  13 - 14     ^L 15+

There is no need to remember the Invite and GF range values.  The magic number is ^*b 25 ^*n 

The pattern is as follows  - 
^d the opening range is always  3  points  
^d the   invite   range is always  2  points

Take the top value of the opening range  and subtract it from  ^*b 25 ^*n   so taking   ^*b17^*n    gives    25 - 17  =  8
so the invite range matching   15 - 17   is   8 - 9   and  GF range is everything above that.

Notice, when partner accepts your invitation with a good middle value (a good 16 here) then you will sometimes play to make a 24 point game.|
